\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 1938.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Your birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was Coubal. Coubal. Also in the parish of Dunross.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 'Til I married. Yes. Except for - being - I was working at the hotel during the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179 summertime}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  you know. But always - always home, that was always home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You had one brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How many years older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 He was - not quite - not quite two years older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were seven your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And he was thirty-three?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 He was thirty-three, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was your mother older or younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179 he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
was just from November to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179 January}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  younger than him. They were both thirty-three, there wasn't much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did he also come from Dunrossness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 He was a fisherman but he was working in Lerwick at - house building or - something like that - some work of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 At the time of his death?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Had he given up the fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't thin
k he'd given up the fishing but - it was seasonal you see and he was working during the winter time in Lerwick. He may have decided to give it up later on I don't know but - the fishing was just in the summer time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So they got other work in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 In the wintertime, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you know if he ever did any other work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No, he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 He never had a croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, his father had a croft. But not him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What happened to the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, a younger }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 brother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 A younger one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was that the usual custom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - not usual custom but - that was how they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What was the usual custom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, the usual custom would have been that the son of the oldest son but then you see my brother w
as only a little boy at the time. So it went - of course my grandfather was alive you see and he was carrying it on all the time and then he passed it on to a younger son. The only son that was - remained to work the croft and nobody questioned that, no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were some people called cotters?
