\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Before she married did your mother ever have a paid job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. She used to work at the hotel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was that the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. It was just - anything, serving at the table and - washing, cleaning up and - at that time,
 well, they didna have any fast rules what they did, they just did anything that came to hand. All - all sorts of jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she also from Dunrossness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, but from the south and, near Sunbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 After she married, did she work before your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But after he died she did washing again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh yes, she did, yes. And very often the visitors coming to the hotel would have to get their washing done while they were there you see, they were obliged to get it - and she did quite a lot of - that sort of work, for visitors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she go every day to the hotel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no. Oh no, not every day but maybe once a week to a big days washing once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she bring any home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, not of that, not of the hotel washi
ng. She did that there. The - the - what she did for some of the visitors she - she would get that done home, she would get that - to do at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Would she bring it back to the hotel herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Oh yes, she would go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 While she was doing the washing can you tell me about the neighbour and how she looked after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh yes, that was - that was my lifelong chum. We went to school together and when mother was away doing her days work and my brother would be staying within while s
he was away and while I was at school, he wasn't able to go to school as a child, he was not very strong to begin with. But - when we come home from school I always came to my chum's house and had a - a hot dinner there and then we would go to our house, 
it was about five minutes walk, and we would get everything tidied up and cleaned up and the fire on before mother come home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And your friend liked cleaning the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh she loved blackleading the stove. Because they didn't have one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What sort of stove did they have then in their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well they had just the low fire, the open fire at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did a lot of the people just have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 A lot, yes. But we did have to get the stove very early on because - them - the fire didna
 burn well and it used to full the house with smoke so they had to get a stove to - keep things going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother cook on that stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did it have one oven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Just one oven at the back - one oven at the back you see and the fire at the front but it was - it was very good, it was }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 squarer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  than this one here you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And the hot top?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You could boil on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes, you could boil several different things on it at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were a child before your father died, did anybody else live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Just your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. My father built the small house for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 After he did die anybody live with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No, we were just - we were always - just - just the three of us, yes, just the three of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She did her washing herself at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you tell me about the clothes in those days, how they got them, did they make them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well they made some of them and - you can always find, in a place like this, somebody who was good at dressmaking. And you could, if you bought the material, you could go and get somebody to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there somebody that your mother knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes. Oh yes. Well for - maybe - really good clothes you could get it done in Lerwick, that was the best but there were several people who would - well in fact, my chum's mother was very good. And she sewed different things 
for me. She did very often. And - I remember once I got a piece of material to make a skirt so I went along and I asked her if she would sew this for me. And she said, no, I won't, She says, just you come with it and I'll show you how to do it for yoursel
f
. And it was the best thing she ever did for me. To show me how to do it. She - she cut it out for me and then she let me see how to work the machine and she started me on it, it was a hand machine, she started me on it and I sewed this skirt myself. I wa
s very proud of her doing that. But she had an idea that I could do it you see and she thought if she let me see just exactly how to do it I would be able to do it again and I - I - sewed quite a lot of things for myself after that. I sewed dresses and -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So that was very useful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh it was, yes. And we didn't have a machine but here was just - just this small hand machine you know and she told me to come and get it any time I wanted I could get her machine and carry it up to our house and sew as mu
ch as I wanted and then bring it back when I was finished. She was a good neighbour so she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Your mother knitted I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What things did she knit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - about that time it was generally shawls. Before they started doing the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Fair Isle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  work. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Fair Isle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 work was only started about - getting towards the end of the '14-'18 war. That was when the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Fair Isle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  knitting - they did it in 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Fair Isle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  before that but that was really when it strayed here to - to the mainland of Shetland shall we say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember the first time you saw people doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, oh yes, I can remember. I was - well, probably finishing school at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were people very excited about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They were, yes, yes, and the - oh everybody if they knew a pattern then they were showing it to somebody else and - and everybody getting -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Before that had there been such nice colours and patterns in the knitting or had it been plain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Well - it was - it was nearly plain, but I remember
 doing - cardigans, maybe white - white a grey or a brown deep band up front and sometimes we did them we stretched more round then, they were fairly long shape then and we would do them with - with bands going round maybe browns and grays and fawns and d
ifferent shades. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But mainly the natural colours. It was only when we started doing the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Fair Isle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  that we started with the - the bright colours, the blues and greens and reds and yellows and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Your mother knitted shawls then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So when you were a child you'd wear a shawl would you if you were cold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - not so much - we - we wore scarves - a scarf.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Round your head and shoulders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well and - and we had - like another - just a cap sort of thing, we would wear th
at and then if it was really cold we would have the scarf tied over that you see in the wintertime. But I never went to school with a shawl. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And no cardigan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, they hadn't started - they started cardigans just before I left school. I can remember my first one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What a change isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It is isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What else did she knit, did they knit traces?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I remember - knitted underwear. She never knitted dresses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Underwear for all the family, men, your father too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
No, I don't remember her knitting - knitting underwear for him. But I wasn't very old then but - we used to do spencers, if you know what a spencer - it's a sort of a bodice, in fact, the first that ever I knitted was spencers. And I did two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How old were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, I think I'd be about six or something like that. And I knitted spencers and I was so keen to knit. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 So I knitted two spencers and mother made them ready and she had some that she'd been knitting and she took me to the shop to sell them you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh boy, I got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You sold them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I sold them. They were baby spencers and I got tenpence each for them. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You must have been thrilled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I was. But the biggest thrill was - when I - was going to buy something for the
m and I bought wallpaper at fivepence a roll. And I got four rolls of wallpaper for my two baby's spencers. We needed five rolls, mother bought the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What did you paper then, did you paper one of your rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she ever buy second hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was that not done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
No. If there was somebody you knew and they had something that they were willing to give you you would accept it. But you would never buy things. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they have jumble sales then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. There were never jumble sales here. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do they have them nowadays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. They're not popular, they're not popular here. You wouldn't be seen wearing something that your neighbour had been going round in.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your father - I think you said the men didn't knit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No, they - the men didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Your father didn't make clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No. His father was a tailor. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But he didn't pass it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about the shoes, where were they bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well they would have been bought somewhere in - in Lerwick I suppose or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 
maybe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  - well the country shops would get them but - a lot of the - more especially the men I think - would go to a local shoemakers and get them made. Made to measure. Because - at that time
 there were hardly a trade that wasna - somebody in the district did follow up, there's - you got stonemasons and you got - joiners, you got - tailors, shoemakers, you could find them all around. And quite a lot of them had been trained, it wasn't just so
m
ething that they had - sort of trained themselves for. My grandfather served his time at the - with a tailor in Lerwick, you see, and learned his trade there and one of his brothers was a shoemaker and he served his time with a shoemaker in Lerwick. So th
ey were quite competent at their work. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about mending the shoes, did your father ever mend them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Nearly all the men could make shoes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 After your father died, what did you do about the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 shoe mending}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - his
 uncle, who was the shoemaker, always mended them for us then. Yes. Until my brother was - came of age that he could do it and then he was quite }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 good}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  at mending shoes. 'Course they were all leather then, there were rubbers or - anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You were saying that people also wore clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they call them clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Clogs. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you tell me about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well they were - the soles was wood and then the what they called uppers was just a piece across the front. The
y didna have anything round the heels. They were just - it was leathers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And they had light ones for indoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Light ones for indoors and heavy ones for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 outdoors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And then they had other things like moccasins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Rifling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
. Yes. Rivlin. It was made from dried cow hide. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was is sewn with thongs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Well it was sewn with - the same - braid as the - the shoemaker's thread. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Up the back heel and up here and then they were holes along the top and a - a piece - bit of twine put in it, to draw it together and then it was tied around the ankle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they wear that outdoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes, they wore them outdoors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What did they wear on Sundays, did they wear boots on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They had - yes, they had their - their boots or shoes for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Special ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, they were kept for Sunday. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179 Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And special clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Where were they put on the other days of the week?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well it would have been just may be what was once be Sunda
y clothes and - worn out as - or - they were put away in white aprons. I can remember some of them wearing white aprons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 All through the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, yes. Bleached. Because they were white, maybe they were made from a - the sack you got the flour in you know, the cotton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did the children wear pinafores or aprons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh yes, yes, they wore pinafores when they were little. Even babies had pinafores. Yes. I can remember baby pinafores. Little frills over the top and frills round the bottom of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember if there was any special season of the year or time of the year when people got new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I - I think to the - to the summer. For the summer. They would - knit during the winter and have a good few - generally shawls tha
t they were - mainly shawls that they were doing then, they would have a good few shawls and then they would - about the time that they'd finished planting their crops then they would get all the shawls ready and get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 them}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  in maybe a basket on their back an
d go two o'clock in the morning and they would leave home to walk to Lerwick. And they had to go from one shop to another to - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 wouldna}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  buy them all at one time. And they would save this and then they would buy what they were needing. With the money they go
t for the shawls And then they would walk back. Over twenty - over twenty miles. Well, they always thought they could walk better after - just after they'd finished because they were - they were having to dig their ground and - a lot of it - they didn't a
ll have ploughs and horses at that time and they were doing a lot of digging and a lot of extra work and they always thought that they walked better when they were in good shape for - after all this hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother ever do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. But I - I don't remember ever walking to Lerwick. She didn't go very much to Lerwick when we were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she knit the shawls to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 sell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How did she sell them then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well sometimes she maybe send them with a neighbours that was going you see and - and they would buy what she wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When your father was alive did he do any jobs indoors in the house to help, did he do washing up or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I - I can't remember anything of that, I suppose he did help anything that he could do he would have done because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You were very young of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You don't actually remember him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I do remember him, yes. I know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But you don't actually remember him doing chores?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh I don't - I don't remember him doing things like that but - I would imagine that he would just do anything he could to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there the idea though that there were jobs that were woman's work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes. There was always that I think. In fact you find it to the present day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It's the same in the South.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I imagine it would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What particular things in those days do you think a man wouldn't do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I - I don't think the men would do the washing unless the - their wife was ill or anything like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about baking and cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no, I - that was a woman's job certainly, unless she was unwell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That would be exceptional?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about things like keeping the fires going, the stove going?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh - I think it - that the men would just take their turn at that, I mean, if anybody }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  handy would - would do the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It wasn't woman's work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Things like decorating, like the putting the wallpaper up and that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh anybody who could did that. It was just anybody's job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Repairs, mending chairs if they broke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 Ashby\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  job again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Everybody did their own repairs at that time, I mean, when there was a man about the house 
he would do all the - odd jobs like that. Even repairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were things ever sent to a furniture shop to be repaired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No. No. They used to do it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were a child did you have any jobs that you did regularly, little tasks, to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I just did anything. Anything, yes. Then of course I was always keen for knitting. I was keen to knit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You didn't have any set things that you had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no. I was never forced to do anything. No. I just did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 After you left school did you go on helping in the house with things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 After I left school I was at Sumb}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 orgh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  hotel. It was a private house then. But I but the Sumborgh hotel now was a private house. I was there one summer and - then we were living down there beside my mother's people for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 a short}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 time because my grandmother took ill and we had to leave our own home and go and live there with her for about three years. Then when we came back to our own house again then the Spiggy hotel was near and I was there for - si
xteen, seventeen, eighteen I think. Just in the summertime. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 There was a family there then was there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It wasn't a hotel then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, it was a hotel then. It was a hotel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not when you left school though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, ye
s, there was a hotel there - it was the same place where my mother used to work before she was married and where she did the days washing, but it was different people who were running it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you do the same kind of general work as she did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I didn't do any washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But you waited at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh yes. Yes. And - did the rooms and - there were not hot water systems then and you had to carry up hot water to the bedroom every morning for people to wash in. And empty it all out again, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What were your hours there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Seven o'clock in the morning until ten o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It must have been terribly tiring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Some days it was. Wednesdays and Sundays was the busy days because Wednesday was the half holiday in Lerwick and
 Sunday was another day, that was two days a week we could look out for getting just busloads of travelers coming up you see for the afternoon or for the day on Sunday. But it was good fun. Oh I liked it, yes. I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You must have been strong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. I was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Some girls, their health breaks down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You were tough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And - well we had interesting people there. We had George Bernard Shaw.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you meet him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. I gave him a drink of water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember if your brother did anything to help you when you were a child or if you helped him at all with anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, he wasn't able to go to school you see but I helped him some with lessons at home. You see, that helped h
im to read and do things like that. And of course mother helped him as well. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So he learnt to read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, oh yes, he came along like that - that he could -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do it at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were a child was there a set time for bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, we - we went to bed, I'm not sure what time but - mother always saw that we went to bed regularly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did this vary with summer and winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I imagine it would. I imagine we would maybe go to bed earlier in wintertime i
n the dark weather and in summertime when it was bright maybe stayed up a bit longer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember if you put yourself to bed when you were about six or seven or if your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I think I put myself to bed }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179 \endash for the most part}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 . I used to sing myself to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179 sleep}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What sort of songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I don't know, I - I imagine it was just maybe - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 bairns'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  hymns or something like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 The croft was usually two rooms wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 One was called a but and one's a ben, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. But and ben.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there any other sleeping space or anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, just the two, yes. Just the two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How did the family sleep then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well there would have been two beds, one - the foot of one to the head of the other you see, slept like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And that would have been in the but?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 In the bed. The ben.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And the but was for cooking and eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes. But was the living. Living part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So you were all of you in the ben?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember what sort of time of the day you had breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well I would imagine it would have been about nine o'clock. About nine o'clock. Of course if we were going to school we had to have it earlier. Because we walked school you see, we had three miles to walk to school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How old did you start going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 At six. Started going to school at six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And you had to walk three miles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, didn't have anything but walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What did you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well we generally had porridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Anything else?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Just porridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, we had tea and maybe a bit of bread or something after, but porridge was the main meal. Yes. It was porridge and milk you se
e and sometimes if we didn't have milk I had porridge and maybe a spot of butter in the middle of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That must have been nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 On Sundays was there anything different for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, we didna - we didna have porridge 
very often on Sunday mornings, no. Maybe cheese or - or maybe an egg sometimes or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were eggs rather }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 precious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I remember we did have a few hens at one time you know when you had - you could feed them on scraps and - have eggs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember when your father was alive did he have breakfast with out in the morning or did he go off earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - I would imagine we all had breakfast at one time. When he - whenever he was home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Because of course he would have been away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, away a lot of the time you see fishing and - and then working away from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 When}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  he was in Lerwick did he have lodgings then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 The next meal of the day, did you have anything about eleven o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well you see I was at school most of the time but - we didn't - we didn't have very much - sometimes we had a cup - maybe a cup of tea or something at eleven o'clock. Depend what we were doing maybe. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you come home for the midday meal or did you have it at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 We had just a cup of cocoa and a piece - at school. At school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you take it with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How did you take the cocoa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - the cocoa was made. Made the cocoa. You had to bring the dry cocoa a
nd the sugar with you. Yes. And - it was all made together in a - big pan and then just dished out to everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 In a mug?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you take peats to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Have you ever heard of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I've heard of it but never - it was never done where I went, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 After school when you came home, what was the next meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, we always had a sort of a dinner or something cooked when we came home from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 At the neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - it wasn't at the ne
ighbours then, it was at our own home you see. When mother was at home she always had something, maybe potatoes sliced and fried up and something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How often in a week would you say you had meat? Did it vary with the season?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. We had meat - well - different times you know but - fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was it more usual to have fish than meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well you see - there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 many}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  butchers shops here at the time and the general things was you would get a sheep killed and slaughtered for the 
winter and then you see you could always have a bit of meat as long as that was and fish was the same, the fish was salted then for the winter. So you always had fish and you always had this salted meat. And could make a tasty meal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When the meats ran out were there some months when you had nothing in the way of meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well they might get rabbits. Set traps for rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was that called poaching round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It wasn't poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 People were allowed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was
 just on common grazing you see. So long as you didn't put the trap anywhere it was going to damage an animal, maybe they would put their foot in it or anything you see then it was all right. In fact, the people were glad to get the rabbits killed because
 they - sometimes there were so many and they were eating the grass.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about shooting birds, did they shoot birds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, not much. No. I never remember us having any - any birds, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have puddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What kind of puddings did they make?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well we were very fond of steamed pudding, fruit steamed puddings. That was something we all liked - I like them yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever have fresh fruit with a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well fruit was something that was very scarce. 
In fact, if we got an orange or an apple at Christmas they were only times we ever saw them. They - they did not - they might have been in the Lerwick shops you know but not in the country shops except just at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Christmas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  And tomatoes - I was a teenager before I got a taste of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 tomato}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 . You couldn't get them in the shops here, you'd get them in Lerwick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about lettuces and cress, did people have that sort of thing in summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, they could grow it but it wasn't something that was very commonly used. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So what green vegetables did people have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, cabbage, always plenty of cabbages and turnips. There was always plenty of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother usually cook cabbage or turnip or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Always, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you something more before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What sort of thing did she cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well it was maybe - we had milk, we had milk and maybe - some kind of bread or scone or something like that. And if we didn't have milk then we had cocoa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she bake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Oh yes, she was a good baker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How often in a week would she bake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well maybe twice or three times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That was with the beremeal was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. We didn't have a croft so we didn't have beremeal unless we got it but - that was flours and - and oat cakes. Yes. I love oat cakes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she ever make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What sort of fruit did they use for jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Rhubarb the Shetland fruit. Yes. I - I always make a full years supply. I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And eat it through the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you keep it in your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179 freezer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. I must keep it in a cupboard. And it keeps well, yes. And we've just finished last years and ready to start this years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother ever preserve fruit or vegetables in a bottle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she ever make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do people eat pickles round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about onions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, but we need to buy them, we didna grow them. Of course not having a croft
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have to buy your own potatoes too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - we would - maybe help somebody lifting their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 potatoes}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  and you could buy the potatoes from them. That was - how it was done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But nothing from the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was any kind of alcoholic drink made, like wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They used to make \{BLANK\}
 but I never saw it. I never saw it done. But I know they used to do it a while ago, what they call Shetland wine, it was done with a beer but I don't know how they did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother ever make any of her own medicines or anything for illness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
No. No. You - you just had what we in Shetland called the brochin, in Scotland it's called gruel. Hot milk and cream of tartar and ginger, sugar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 If you weren't well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. You got - if you got a cold you got that and it was - well it was - you would maybe sweat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179  after}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  it and - and it - it broke - it broke the strength of the cold.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You had a few hens, you were allowed to keep a few hens on the croft were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well just - we had them fenced in at the end of the house. They didn't roam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have any pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Just the hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Just the hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No cows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Who fed the hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh it would have been mother who would have fed the hens but - well I fed them sometimes, I can remember feeding them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you ever remember having meat out of a tin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not as a child. No. No. It was unknown then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Anything at all out of tins do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not salmon or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, oh no, no. Not even milk out of a tin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 The fruit in the pudding, would that have been dried fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Sultanas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they have dried peas in your house, dried beans?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, well we didn't have them 
very often, not the beans, we had, maybe had peas sometimes. Of course we could get lentils and rice, that was the main thing for making soup. Lentils and rice. And Barley. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Made with the bones of the sheep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes. And you see if you had
 this salted mutton, a very small bit could make a nice pot of soup and if you had that and maybe potatoes to - after to eat the bit of meat with the potatoes you were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever remember your mother having less }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179 food}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  so that the others could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes. I remember mother telling me that when she got us both to bed and gone to - we'd gone to sleep she would stand and look at us and wonder if we'd had enough to eat that day and I wondered how much she'd had when she was wondering if we'd had enough.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 There was a shortage of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well, it was just that we didn't - couldn't - she couldn't afford anything more. It was a - it was a struggle to - to - too feed - yes, yes, it was. So I - I imagine that there were sometimes she 
might have - maybe could have done with something she didn't have. But she never complained. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When your father was alive was there also a shortage or were things better then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - he would have been earning you see and that would have made 
things maybe a bit easier but I can remember my uncle, my mother's brother, when he would have been finished the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 fishing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 for the year and - and got this money for the year, he would send us a - a - maybe a boll of flour. See that was a big - hundred and fo
rty pounds. Yes. A big boll of flour, I can remember him doing that more than once. And also sending us fish. Maybe fresh fish or salt fish. So he helped us. And of course my grandfather would have done the same, mother's father, would have done the same,
 sent us something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about the people on the croft where you had your house, didn't they help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not just an awful lot. No. They were kind of sticky like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They weren't the kind to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not - not like - no, not like even our neighbours. No. They couldn't help it I suppose, it was just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Their character?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Just how they were, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you know if she asked them and they refused?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, she never asked for anything. She wouldn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I suppose it would have hurt her to ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She must have been a wonderful person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
She was. She really was you know. She was - she was the kind that - she always walked tall. She held her head up and she would say, if you don't hold your head up yourself nobody's going to hold it for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she have a fear of getting into debt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh she did, yes. She always said, never buy anything }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 unless}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  you can pay for it. That's - how we were brought up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You were telling me how people used to get into debt with a shop, the lairds shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, they - they would - well I think that the laird would have the shop and the laird would have the - the fishing boat you see and it }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 all turned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  into the laird and it just depended if they made a good 
season and could pay everything at the end they were all right but - if they couldn't then, well - they would be - in debt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Your mother's parents had that problem did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well they - they were just in the same - boat as every one else, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember something about the table manners then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were you allowed to talk at meals, you and your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 Well I don't think we talked just an awful lot, we maybe talk a little, we weren't told to sit still and not 
speak at all you know but - I think we was fairly moderate And at a very early age we were learned to use fork and knife when we were very young, people remarked on it.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 About three years old or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not much older than that. And we were made to say thank you for everything we got.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were they particular how you held your knife and fork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh I think so, I think we were trained from being well - yes, I think we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 If your mother cooked something and you didn't like it could you refuse it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well we did sometimes I suppose. But then she didn't very often cook anything we didn't like I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Nowadays children are so fussy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It didn't happen so much then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 If you had just not felt like eating what would has have said about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I don't know, she would have -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Would she have tried to persuade you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I reckon she would, yes, I imagine she would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you ever remember having the food brought back again at the next meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No. No, I never remember her doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 If you wanted another helping, could you ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Could you ask if you wanted something passed to you, if there was salt on the table or something you could ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You didn't have to sit quiet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no, No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember if you wanted to bring a book or a toy to the table could you do that during a meal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I never remember any objections. But maybe we just didna do it then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I don't think there were any hard and fast rules. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you'd finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When we - yes, when we'd finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have to wait 'til everyone finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I don't think it was ever imposed. No,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember if when you sat for the meal you had the same place always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. We always sat in our same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother serve up the food onto dishes from the pots or straight from the pots onto plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh I can't remember. I imagine soup was just dished from the pot into the plates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in the conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, we were never - there was never anything said but it was like
 an understood thing that you didn't chip in when older people were speaking. I think we didn't try to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It just wasn't the done thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, it wasn't done, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember in those days what your mother and father thought about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh it was - it was a bad thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you think there's more bad language than there used to be or hasn't it changed on Shetland in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well there's some that seem to swear all the time, and there's others that don't swear at all so I think it's just a good mix.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you did something and your parents didn't like it what would happen, would they say something?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh they would -yes, oh yes, I've been checked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they ever actually punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't think -
 oh I might have got a little - oh, no, not - not - not to be hurtful, just as much as letting me know that I didn't have to do that again. I don't think that hurts anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were you ever sent to your room without supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 If you did anything wrong when you were very small would your father sometimes check you and your mother or was it just the one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I - I can't remember - I can't remember him ever helping to check. Well I was too small then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you reme
mber how your mother brought you up to behave towards your brother do you remember the ideas she had about how brothers and sisters should be to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well we just had to be kind and we just had to be tolerant. There was no favouritism.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember what sort of people your mother hoped you and your brother would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well she would want us to be respectable and - truthful and honest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she somebody who talked a lot about that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, it was more by example. And - well just - as I've said before, if you can't afford a thing wait 'til you can.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she - did she talk to you ever about worries and things or did she keep it to herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She never said very much about worries. She - kept herself - yes, she didna annoy anybody you know, never, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were you a child who got worried and upset about things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I'll tell you what did worry me was my brother went - I'd been used to him being ill and if he went out of sight I got worrie
d about that, in case anything had happened to him. That was the - the main thing that worried me when I was a child.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you tell your mother this worry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh she knew - yes, she knew. Yes. Yes, she knew that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you talk to her much, was she the sort of person that liked to talk a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh yes, and she read an awful lot too. Yes. She used to read from the papers to us. Well it was the Christian Herald was the main paper that we got when we were children and there were always stories in that and she used to read all the stories for us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 wonderful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  when you think how busy she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. But she was knitting at the same time as - she - was - knitting and reading, yes. And she used to recite poems that they }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179 learned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  at the 
school. Something about the babes in the wood and - that kind of thing and - and when it came to the sad bit then I was standing and sobbing at the back of the chair you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she ever tell stories too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. She would tell stories, the kin
d of stories that have father would have told to them when they were small you see because - well then they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
no television they had no wireless see, they were just - they relied on - on - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Learning from other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, and stories - 
oh - I would imagine sometimes your maybe your old man would sit and make up a story as he was going along, just something to amuse a family of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1513370\charrsid9600179 bairns}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were they about fairies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Sometimes, yes. Sometimes. One story - I can remember mother was say
ing, was, her father, they were small and her father was telling them a story and he was sitting and doing some work in the middle of the floor you see and that was about some queer person that somebody had seen coming along the road and they were coming 
nearer and nearer and nearer and he was sitting with a clog like and when he came to the bit, they were just coming up for the door, he threw the clog at the door and - it made a noise and they were all - ooh - thought there was someone funny coming in.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were they all about ghost quite often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I think so, yes. But of course I never believed in ghost altogether. No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did a lot of people of your mother's age though believe in this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Some - some were very superstitious but mother wasn't superstitious. Oh no, she wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember if when you had a birthday there was anything to make it different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 We couldna afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You didn't have your chum in for tea or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, never made any difference of a birthday. It was just as any other day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Christmas. We always hang up our stockings on Christmas Eve and if there was an apple or an orange round or - something, just anyt
hing that we might find and mother always said if she had a sixpence a shilling she could put it in our stocking because the first thing we did in the morning if we found money was to give it to her. So she said if she had a shilling she could always drop
 it in a stocking because she knew she would get it back in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Is it true that in Shetland New Year is more important than Christmas in some ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I don't know, the one is just much the same as the other but one time it was maybe more so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 More sort of celebrations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. First footing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 The first person in the door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
The - they've - they've started more of that now lately I think. But - well I don't remember much about that when I was a bairn. But, no, they do - they do sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have anything special to eat on Sunday for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes, I think we always had something a little bit more elaborate than during the week, it was something that - distinguished Sunday from the rest of the week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I said they didn't have - they called it tarties didn't they, tarties and fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. They didn't have the fish see. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They'd have some meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember on Christmas Day if you had anything different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, I th
ink that we always had something that distinguished Christmas - well maybe we got something from somewhere - I had an aunt in Edinburgh always sent us a parcel Christmas. It was always a treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have a fowl or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Sometimes we - we had that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have any musical instruments in your home, did your father play anything when he was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 He had a fiddle. And - we had a small }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 accordion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 That}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  was all that we had as children was this small -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not very much I don't think, my brother played on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 accordion}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  but - but I didn't play very much, maybe a little you know but not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, she wasn't musical at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You say women didn't play fiddles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. But she wasn't - she wasn't ever musical, couldn't - and my father could sing but not mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you and your brother sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, we both sang. We must have got it from our father's side, not mother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever make music together, you and your brother and your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, I can remember singing hymns on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When he was still alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. When he came home from church he'd be maybe at church and then come home and I can remember him sitting at the table having te
a you see, used to have his Sunday shirt, white shirt, and then we would maybe sing hymns after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Would he play the fiddle then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I think it was just mainly singing together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember if your mother or father ever played any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes, we did have some childish games you know that we used to play like - I don't know, I don't remember the names of them. We did play games that we were in the habit of playing just inside the house. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were they things like snakes and ladders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, yes, we had that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And ludo?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 Ludo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 , yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did people play with cards, did you have cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. We had cards but the - other - some - some folk didna believe in cards you know. That was - that was especia
lly the Baptists. Yes. They were more like that. We were Church of Scotland you see and - but the Baptist were more against cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How was Sunday kept in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well it was just - we did - we never knitted on Sunday. Oh no. Knitting was work and we just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Could you read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You were allowed to do recreational things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes. Could do anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It wasn't a sort of sad and solemn day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no. No. And then went to Sunday school and - church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Every Sunday did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well - not - well not especially to church but we - we went to Sunday school. And I can remember - going a lot to church, after my father died. And I can remember; going to church before my father died. We all went to church together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were you in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I was in the choir, I'm in the choir here. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were a child did the choir have any special treats or outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were you paid for the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they have a Sunday school outing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. They had a - kind of outing - well no outing, a - a Christmas party, well it was just kind of a concert and you got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You said that your mother used to read the Christian Herald?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That was a newspaper was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes, it was a weekly. At the time that we had it, it's still in publication you know, yes, yes, there would have been maybe two serial stories and a complete story. There were lots of - two sermons, and lots of short readings, well, pa
ragraphs about one thing and another you know that was going on and - a Sunday school lesson and quite a lot of reading in it and it cost a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she read everything in it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh I think so, yes, I think so. It was about the only - the 
paper we got you see and - well, money wasna very much. No, not very plentiful at that time so - a penny a week you made use of all the reading that was in it, you did read it, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you pass it on to any other family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I don't remember - I d
on't think so. Quite a number of people in the district took it at that time you see, it was really about all the outside papers you had, there were no daily papers then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did people lend books to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Oh yes, they would. School prize
 books you know, we got school prize books and my brother, he was a great reader and whenever I got a book he would come and get my book to read. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 
Of course I liked boys' stories when I was going to school. The teacher nearly always gave me boys' stories.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well the World of Ice and - that's R.M. Ballantyne's books, I loved them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Treasure Island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. That's one of them. And the teacher nearly always gave me a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 \endash }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  boys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  book for a prize.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And the Coral Island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, yes. And I remember the same boy, he used to have the Boys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  Own papers, that was come monthly or something and we used to get that to read from him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did everybody get a prize at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I think everybody got some sort of a prize, maybe a - later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have any books in the house that hadn't been got as prizes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, we did have some. Maybe got them from somebody, you know, present of a book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother read books as well as the Christian }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 Herald}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She liked reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She liked reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she ever read aloud from the books to you as well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember your father reading at all when he was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I can't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 so much about him you see, not - not the small things like that, not little things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You remember about him having tea with his white shirt on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you tell anything else you remember about him, anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I seem just to remember him about the house you see when he was home at weekends and - but - I think }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10553796\charrsid9600179 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 his death - the shock of his death seemed to black out most of that with me. It was a period about that time that my recollections weren't just so clear. I think it was - I think it was a matter of shock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you actually remember being told about his death?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh I remember, he - he died you see at home. And I remember him dead because the old folk at that time, a lot of them, his mother, my grandmother, had an idea that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 if}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  you laid a child's hand on the brow of a dead person they wouldn't be frightened. And I can remember, it was either her or my aunt taking me where the remains was lying you know and laying my hand on his }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 brow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 . And that feeling - I could always recall that fe
eling. That cold brown. But I - strange to say, before he died, I was frightened to go to sleep. I couldn't go into the next room unless there was a light on and I could only go out the door in the dark as far as the light was shinning out the door, but -
 as - whenever he died that fear all left me and I could go any - it left me completely. I - I've heard some say the same. Experience the same - the same thing happening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When she wanted you to did she tell you she wanted you to go in and put your hand on his brow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I think it was me grandmother did that. I think it would have been my grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you struggle against it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't think so. I don't think so. We just accepted it. I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did many people come and look at the body?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, it was quite common for people to come. Yes. And - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 funeral}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  weeks were - when it ended.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Men and women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Women - I never recollect seeing any women going to a funeral in Shetland, not here. They may do in Lerwick but never in the country.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not today still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no. No, not - no not still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did the men wear black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Generally there's bowler hats and - black ties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did the body lie for quite a long while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 About three days. About three days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And did people sit with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. I don't think so. It was all right to be left alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 After the funeral was there any kind of a supper or tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No,. No. At one time - they used to meet in a small hall and - of course they were wal
king long distances at that time, and they had biscuit and wine. They served them biscuit and wine and that was stopped when I was very young, I can remember them speaking about it you see, but that was stopped, that serving of wine and biscuit. Maybe whe
n people got more transport and things like that. And you see at that time they had to carry the coffin all the way, they had no - they carried it, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No horses were ever used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, not - not here. No. Of course now it would be a mini bus or - something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So when your father died, you remember the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes. Oh yes. But they took my brother and me to my grandfather's house at that time they took us - of course it was no distance from the one house to the other but they took us out of the house at that time you see, they took us to the grandfather house.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they draw the blinds in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Oh yes, even the near neighbours had their blinds drawn. And - the road where the coffin would be passing, the
 blinds were all drawn along the road as the funeral passed. That was - customary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do they still do that today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I don't know if they do it just so much because now it's going past in cars. Makes such a difference, yes. But when they were - 
when they were having to walk and to carry - blinds were always drawn along the road. And they would keep them on - at that time, they would keep them on all that day and lift them the following morning. Now, they generally lift the blinds while the men a
r
e away at the funeral so that when they come back the blinds are up. I think it's much better. You know, it did keep a felling of sorrow about the house when the blinds had to be down the whole of that day, especially if it was summertime. Blinds down the
 
whole day, you couldna lift the blinds the 'til the following morning. But now, they - they generally do have them, the blinds away by the time that the men come back again. Consider there's no longer death in the house you see, so - lift the blinds, well
 that - I think - I think it's best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did the womenfolk who didn't go to the funeral put on black clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 Well you know mourning was a thing that was very, very much observed here. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
For a father or a mother or a brother they would wear it three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well for a - for a husband they - they put it on for life. Of course that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 
altered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 , my mother before she died, she - she didna wear bright colours you know but she - she did remove from black, she didna wear black al
l the time but the - well I think the war, the first war when we had clothing coupons and everything, I think that did an awful - did - well, both the wars made a difference like that. When we had clothing coupons you had to get coupons for everything tha
t you got and you didn't have them and I think that made a great difference to the wearing of mournings. But when my father died I was put in absolute black. Everything was black. Can you imagine a bairn hardly seven year old dressed in black. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 And every relative that died, cousins or anything, you'd to get on something black.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 People must have been black nearly all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well they were. The most of my youth was spent in black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have any feelings about it, did you dislike black or didn't you mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well I - it was just something that was done then. Accepted it. But I say now that I feel that I wore all my mournings when I was a child and - well uncles and that - well I didna put on black when uncles died or aunts in recent years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 still}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  wear mourning though round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Not nearly so much as it used to be. I see some not even for a brother they don't put anything. You see, they used to - to put on - quite a - lot, well a hat and gloves and maybe a coat and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they have crepe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It must have been a big outlay and expense for a woman who'd just been bereaved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, it was. I remember my mother's - black }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 clothes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  she got when my father died. Of course it was the long skirt and it w
as crepe from the knee to the bottom on the skirt and the coat, it was a costume you see, and the coat reached down to - to the knee almost, it was a long - it was a lovely - a lovely style. Well that had a deep piece of crepe round the bottom of it as we
l
l. It had crepe cuffs, crepe cuff and collars and lapels and seams up here and here and at the back were covered in crepe. Then she had a crepe hat. Well that crepe fall at the back, what they, call the fall. It was folded, you know, it was kind of like a
 shape when it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 folded up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 and you had to mind she didn't sit on it it was so long down. And then a black veil over her face. That was the - that was the depth of the mourning then. But then you don't see anything like that now. Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she wear that dress for some years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She did. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 For Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was a best dress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 just}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  for Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And even she didn't go to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no. Oh no. Just men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did young boys go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well the - maybe when they were coming an a bit - leaving school age. Not - just very young ones, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was a Bank Holiday something that was noticed or made much of when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I never knew what it - never knew they had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I don't know. It was something I knew nothing - nothing about, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about going away for a holiday, did you ever do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - the first time I was so far as Lerwick was when I was twelve years old. Never been to Lerwick before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What did you think of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh I thought it was quite - quite good. We were staying with cousins in Lerwick. And it was quite all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179  right}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 . We was there I think a fortnight. They had been coming to us you see, different times and then they wanted us to come to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was that on your mother's side, the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes, yes. It was 1915. And at that time they were - the Navy had their - their drill at Lerwick there at the fort and they marched to the bagpipes every morning. I just loved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were there still a lot of sailing boats in Lerwick harbour then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, oh yes, they would have been at that time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That was a holiday, you felt it was a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Oh yes, it was a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. We were all - my mother and my brother and myself, we were all there. And it was a - really a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How did you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well there were cars by that time. We went with a car.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Somebody gave you a lift did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
No. I think the cousins maybe paid the expenses, I think they did, the cousins who wanted us. See there were no cars bases in the country at that time, the cars were in Lerwick and they sent this car down for - they - they took me - they had been dow
n and they took me along with them and then they sent a car down for my mother an brother. So I think really they paid that expenses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you go again or was that just the one time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I was - it was a year }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  two before I went again. Because - well there were no cars }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 the country, not many at that time, they were just beginning to come in the country districts about that time and - well you just didna feel that hiring car was - money was short you see, money was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did people just drop in on their neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. They would just - the door was open and somebody would come in with their knitting and - and - that would have been in the evening.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 About what time did people drop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh maybe five or six o'clock and they would stay 'til after they'd had their supper and then they would - go - walk - walk home again.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That would be about what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh maybe eleven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They'd stay }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 quite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You would give them supper if they called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. They got just what you had. It was a - easy kind of living. There was no - it was no invitations you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever extend an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, you would be telling somebody to come, be sure and come. But I mean it wasn'
t a case of setting a day for them or an hour for them or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You'd say come and see us?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes. They would just come when they felt like it. And you would do the same, you would say, oh we'll go and visit so and so tonight and - used to make ready and go. And you never knocked at the door when you came. You just opened the door and walked in.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do people still do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well not so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They knock now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well not so much maybe knocking but - they'll say when they're going 
to come, you know when they're going to come. But I think T.V. and other machines has knocked out a lot of that visiting. They have plenty of entertainment at home that - T.V. and - and the knitting machines even because they're working - anybody who has 
knitting machines, they're working at them all the time and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So they cant' chat and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 
They can hardly speak to their own family about the house, because they're having to count the rows and stitches all the time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It's a
 very unsociable thing I think. That's progress, well they call it progress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about any day of the week for visiting, any particular day of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh it didna matter, didna matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 On Saturdays and Sundays did people come in in the daytime then or just in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
No, it was - it didna matter. Sundays was a general time maybe when they would come after the morning service, after they went from a distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And stayed for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And stayed for - yes, and then go t
o the evening service at night and then go home again you see, they were staying there between services at somebody's house nearer the church than they were themselves. One time on Saturdays all the shoes had to be cleaned and all the potatoes peeled for 
Sunday. Everything of that kind was done on Saturday so that there were nothing done on Sunday but what was absolutely essential.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was like that in your home too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was - it was that everywhere. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What was cooked then, just the meat or whatever it was or was that cold?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - no, no, it would be cooked. But everything that could be done was done on Saturday. Yes. And all the shoes cleaned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And the clothes all ready I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 If your mother went visiting in the evening did she take you with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. She never left us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Children were taken out quite late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. But then - but maybe wouldna been so late as that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 
If you had children with you, you wouldna stay so long really.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did people not have baby sister and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh no. Of course it - was all right where there were a lot of folk in the house you see. We were different, we were just the three of us. But where there were plenty of folk about a house then there w
ere always somebody in to look after us. Anybody who needed it, either old or young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember any temperance club at the church or anything to try and get people not to drink }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  your church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't - maybe they had temperance lecture
s different times and I can remember in the Sunday school temperance lessons, you know, it's a Sunday school lessons. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 
About - you know this about - text - stick them up and when you're walking in a strong drinkers' region.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But nothing to join up a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
No, not when I was very young. Later on there was a branch of the B.W.T.A. here one time but - that faded out after about - I suppose anybody who started it, maybe when they were away somebody else wasn't so enthusiastic about it and it just faded out.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 In your family did you say grace or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 My brother. Yes. Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, oh yes, always when we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you say them to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When your father was alive did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I don't remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember any clubs or institutes to do with the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - there's a - we have a Woman's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 Guild}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  you know that's been going on for over seventy years. Oh yes, my mother was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 of the first to join. At seventy-two years I think when she joined. Yes. Seventy-two years and she joined - I have her membership card still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she go regularly to meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well she would have gone before she was young before she was married but then when we were small she didna leave us to go to any - to anything of that. But then - in later years then we both went together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What sort of things did they do in the Guild?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well - the ladies all had their knitting with them you know, that's a foregone conclusion. But - somebody would have given a talk or - read a portion of scripture and some hymns and prayers and - it was very much just a - a kind of a servic
e but you had your knitting with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they have any tea or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh yes, yes. Yes, we all had tea. Before that there was what they called the Scots Girls Friendly Society. My - my mother was a member of that too and - before the - before this Guild was started. She was a member of the Scots Girls Friendly Society. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 And that - is going on yet in Scotland but they had a very, very strict rules because they wouldn't accept as a member any girl who had fallen. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And - and I - when I read over th
at later on I kind of questioned it. I think - I thought it was the wrong attitude. Yes, it was the wrong attitude. They were there to keep out anyone who had made a mistake. They should have been trying to lift them up again I thought.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do they still do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well I don't know what they do now because it's not here. But they do have branches in the South but - but not in Shetland. I - I - well I just question they motive and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It's like the mothers union in England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It's not to have divorced women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Would it have been the same here with the Guild do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well they're not so many divorced people in Shetland. But - with the Guild, I don't think the Guild - the present Guild ever asked any questions }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 like that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 , they were supposed to be there to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 enlighten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 the women and to try to lift them up if they were down and - certainly I would say that was the - the - the proper attitude, yes. But it seemed to me to be the wrong thing if a girl had made a mistake to ban her from being a member.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It's not a Christian attitude is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It's not the Christian attitude, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember or did you ever hear if your father took an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I think about that time, I remember the firs
t - the first election that I remember anything about was everybody saying, vote for Westman. Westman was apparently the - I think he was a Tory. But - I don't know if my father had any - I don't know, I never - I never heard him say anything about that, 
no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And your mother never told you if he had views of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 It}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  was just something that - we didn't take up very strongly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was your mother politically interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not to any great extent.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Shetland does have a famous Liberal Member of Parliament?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you think that your mother was more inclined to the Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I think so. I think so. We considered that the Tories were the - the moneyed people. The Liberals were liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever hear anything about the Labour when you were a young girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, the Liberal was the - was the - party who did most for Shetland, a long while ago. And the I know the folk would }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 inclined}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  for the - the Liberal yet. Of course there is more leaning to La
bour in the last - years. But - Liberal always gets in in Shetland and - well personally I think I would be keenly disappointed if Mr Grimmond hadn't got in. Just because of Mr Grimmond. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 People admire him as a man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you 
remember any issue anything that happened, your mother talking about it, like what she thought about the difference between the rich and the poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No. No, I - no, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She didn't talk about that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Any of your uncles or anyone like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you think perhaps men talked about that more to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Maybe they did. It's quite possible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Women got the vote for the first time in 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember your mother voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes. And I can remember the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  Herald was a picture of Mrs Pankhurst on the outside of it when she chained herself to the railings. We thought that was very exciting you know. Picture was in the Christian Herald, front page.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was quite dramatic really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother eve tell you who she voted for or what party she voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, that was something that we never really discussed. No, we had ever discussed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She wasn't a member of a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Your mother was a member of the Guild?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You say that after she was widowed she didn't leave you and go to anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Not - she - she just went to anything where she could take us - along with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And that wasn't the kind of thing you took children to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she have any sort of entertainment or anything relaxing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, nothing outside just the family and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And people calling in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 People calling in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she have friends at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
You get the impression in those days neighbours were friends and friends were neighbours and there wasn't a distinction in some areas, was it like that on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 Shetland}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I imagine it 
would be you know but - well the time of - shall we say a time of trouble everybody would gather round you, and everybody would help you. Of course there were always the faithful who were there all the time. But - and then maybe others who - well, came at
 a special time. But - Shetland people were very friendly like that, helpful, oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Would you know when your father was alive if he belonged to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Don't think so. Don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did the men go to pubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well there were nay pubs here. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there any sport that people did, did the men play cricket or football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well the - the boys used to play football. It wasna serious, you know, it wasna like having real teams, it was just maybe at Christmas or New Year or something like that they would have a game of football among them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No teams then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, it was just a - just more for the fun of it and playing a game but it wasna really serious what football is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Is there any kind of Shetland sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were a child did you ever play with a ball or a bat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. We played - played ordinary games like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Throwing the ball and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there any racing when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. NO.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not dogs or pigeons or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, oh no, not here, nothing of that came here, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember if you father or mother belonged to any clubs for saving?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no. There were nothing - I never - no, I don't - I never heard anything of that at that time, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Boot clubs and sick clubs and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about insurance, would she have paid insurance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - the first about insurance was - fishermen and workers like that, the fir
st - letters about that came just about the time that my father died. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she helped by that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not 'til she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 fifty-five}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  and then she got a widow's pension because had be lived the job that he was in would have been an insured job. But he had never paid anything you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were a child you had your great chum who lived nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have other children you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Different ones. Well, with any of them round about, but that was my special one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she your friend for many years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She's been my lifelong friend, we're friends yet. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She still lives near you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She lives near where I lived before - near up to Spiggie. She was married, her husband died a few years ago, s
he had two daughters. One of them is married and lives in Ipswich. She's married to R.A.F. and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 other one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  - is being }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 Librarian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 at Edinburgh University for some time, or working in the library there. She hasn't passed finally for her librarians yet but she's
 going to run the library to finish her course there - to qualify as librarian. She's - and she feels it I think that she doesn't want to teach. Yes. She's clever, very clever but just - well she did teach a little and I think they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 weren't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  very kind, some of the bairns
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Children can be very unkind can't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They can be, yes. So she's had her little cross to bear.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were at school do you remember any children who were a bit left out of things, or teased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not too bad here, no, not too bad in this school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember anyone at all who was outcasted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
No. But I remember one - our last day at school and during the dinner break every girl in the school had a shot at leading on her arm a little bit along the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Because everybody liked her so well. And - it wasn't many years after that that she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she a very good child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She was very nice, very nice and very nice to everybody. But it was something I never forgot was her last day
 at school. And every one had just a little bit of a shot leading on her arm along the road, walking up and down the road. I never saw - it with any other one but her, but - that's something - she died young, yes. It's something I never forgot. And I reme
mber telling her sister, she had a younger sister, of course she couldn't know about that but I - I remember telling the sister that once and she was so grateful that I'd told her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It's a lovely thing to think of isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you used to play was it all around about outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you play in houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. We - we played inside too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You weren't chased out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were there sort of flower gardens at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well some had maybe little but the gardens were at the front of the houses and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 A very small bit one time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 We had - well you know, the hardy annuals like marigolds and chrysanthemums and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you do it yourself as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, we - yes, oh yes, we helped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you played with other children were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 allowed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  to get dirty, get your clothes dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh we just - tumbled around and - but then you see, when we come h
ome from school, the school clothes was off and - we had old clothes on. We didna play about after school with school clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They were saved for the next day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Saved for the next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When did the children have all clean clothes, was that for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How did people manage for bathing then, they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 didn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  have running water did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. We used to have to carry it in - was a big tub or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they sort of have a regular day for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I think it's Saturday - Saturday was the main time for - for the big wash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were a child do you remember if you could play with anyone you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 There was no child your mother told you not to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no. No, no. Never any restrictions like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It shows how nice a community it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, it was, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 As a schoolgirl did you have any hobbies, besides your knitting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes - well I was very fond of sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 After your neighbour taught you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. And - crochet. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do a lot of Shetland people do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Not an awful lot. But it was my chum's mother who learnt me - started me off on crochet. And I've done quite a bit of crochet but I never keep any of it myself, I give it all away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you collect any things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, I collected -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 As a child did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No, I never went fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Or for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, we went walks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you go for walks for pleasure or to get to a certain place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But you would say, let's go for a walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I did. It was one of my - childhood ambitions. My three ambitions was a - an organ and a bicycle and a sewing machine. And I got them al
l. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When did you get the organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh - it was after I left school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How did you get the money for that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - it was a neighbour who was selling it and he said - it had been his daughter's and he said, if I would only tak
e it I could just pay a little in on it now and again. And that was what I did. Did because he wanted it - he said he didn't want it to go anywhere else, he wanted me to take it and he - he said I could just pay for it as I could but - of course we paid f
o
r it as fast as ever we could. And it was through him that we had a shop, that was through him that I got my bicycle too, he was given a bicycle for his daughter and he - he got one or two extra and he wanted me to take one so that the daughter - we could
 have company, we could go out together But I got - I got the sewing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 machine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 later on. One of my uncles was going to Edinburgh for - he was wanting furniture and he said was there anything we would like. And I said, oh I'd like a sewing machine. He was gett
ing it secondhand. So he came back with this sewing machine and it was twenty-nine shillings. A - a treadle machine you know. It's now going now you know I got it over thirty years ago but it's all I'll ever need. It was secondhand but it was very good. S
o I got my - all my ambitions. All my ambitions, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever have any pocket money as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well we might have got a penny now and again but that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It wasn't a regular a thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no. It wasn't. We never looked for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you got it do you remember what you spent it on or did you save it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well we might have bought - of course you could get a ha'pennyworth of sweeties then. But it wasn't all spent at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember anything like a cinema before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
What they called magic lanterns. That was still pictures, you know, with a big projector affair and - we used to see still pictures. It was generally missionary meetings you know and - at - yes, in connection with the church. Missionary meet
ings and there would be some Minister would come and he would show you maybe Palestine and - yes, things like that. Some place where the church held mission work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about a play, did you ever see acting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Any concerts at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, well there were some concerts locally. And maybe some doing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179 little bit
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  of acting and sketches there. But nothing - I mean nothing that we - anybody that was talented or - it was just a place to - generally public.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about fiddlers, men playing the fiddle all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No. I never - I never heard anything of that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about pets, did you have anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Had a cat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What was it called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Rosie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was it yours or the family's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, it belonged to us all. Yes. Yes, belonged to us all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember if your mother was ever ill when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, she was a very healthy woman and she was never really ill. She might have had 'flue or something but never an illness. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you ever remember anybody coming to help her at any time with her work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Not housework. No. Her brothers helped to cut the peat. But she did a lot of the cutting of peat too. And she used to - we had a - the roof that had to be tarred and she very often did that. On her own, yes. She not had the money to pay somebody for }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 doing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  it and she just did it herself. That was before my brother came age that he could do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was your brother quite strong when he got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, he got - he got quite strong as he grew older, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Where did he get the peats from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well it was maybe two miles away. And she - we - and of course we didn't have a horse and cart and she used to bring them home in a wheelbarrow, yes. Very hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did some}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703962\charrsid9600179  people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  carry them in baskets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. But not so much - no so much when I was young. They used to do more of that before.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That was going out then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, but - yes it was. There more horses and carts. And of course sometimes - we would get someone
 to bring home some with a cart you know, somebody had a - a horse and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 cart}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 and very often maybe somebody would bring it, cart load of peat home and they wouldn't have anything for bringing it. You know, you met with that kind of folk as well. They weren't
 all hard creatures who wouldn't help you, but then you didn't ask them to do it unless you thought you had something to pay them. But if they wanted to do it for nothing for you - or maybe you could help them with something that - some of their work. The
 one helping the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Would they then suggest it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Oh yes, they would, they would maybe brought home a - a cart load of peat and - and; they wouldn't have anything for it then, what can we do to help you? We can maybe - gather potatoes or - something like that. Some help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Your grandmother lived near Sumburgh didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, my mother's mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was your other grandmother alive too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But you were closer to your mother's mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What other relatives lived nearby, you had an uncle who was a cobbler, was that you father's uncle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That was my father's uncle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Your great-uncle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did he live nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, he lived near and - and another one, his brother was just a crofter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you see them quite often?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When your father was alive do you remember anything about his friends or if he had friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well it would be just mainly neighbours who were - kind of - always be friend
s I mean. Well we just - had maybe a kind of a sticky feeling that we didn't want to go too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You weren't always made welcome?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was that rather unusual among relatives do you think, for people to be like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well they - they might have been. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 In Shetland at that time before 1918 did you think of the people around where you were as being divided into different social classes?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no, everybody was alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You didn't think in terms of classes of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No. The minister may have been maybe a bit above the ordinary class. But that was all. You respected the minister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were there any sort of school teachers or people around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well not just in our immediate neighbourhood. Not living in 
our immediate neighbourhood. But the - the schoolteachers you certainly respected the - the schoolteachers. You wouldna talk to the schoolteacher like what you would have done to a neighbour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there a laird round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, he was - a fair distance away. We only saw him very very occasionally so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What was he like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I don't know, we just paid the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 He didn't mix with the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Well not in our district you see, he didn't live in our district. He was a - he was a fair distance away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Among the ordinary people, they were all the same were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes, they were all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 There were no distinctions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no class distinctions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were there any families who were considered to be rather rough, not respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well there would have been a rough one here and there, not the whole families but might have been one in a family who was kind of black sheep. That - you find that anywhere. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were you brought up to curtsey to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were you brought up to call anybody sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did nobody do that round where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not even the minister was called sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember men touching their caps to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well it might have been somebody that they were thinking was a bit - but not to their neighbours. Not to their neighbours, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were there any people that owned shops round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were they just the same as the ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, but - they were liable to get maybe on a committee.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were they considered more important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well - I think that they were - thought maybe that they maybe knew a lot more than just the ordinary people. But that's gone now you know. Oh yes. That went - I would say that went out with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 war}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 The first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
No, more with the last war really but - you no longer put a merchant on a committee just because he was a merchant. It was more by - the sign of what the man was rather than his position. But at one
 time certainly the merchant was a merchant or somebody like that they was - liable to be put on a committee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were they called merchants the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there a family of shopkeepers near you which you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did the children go to the same school as the other children,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Would the womenfolk talk to the other women just in the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Oh, there was no difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They didn't consider themselves better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Oh 
no, they didn't. None of that. No. The - the merchant who lives near us we used to get something from him every Christmas maybe, apples and oranges or something like that. It was very nice of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were they on visiting terms with the other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember anybody, any families who thought they were a bit better than other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 There was nothing like that at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about the different churches, you were Church of Scotland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Church of Scotland - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What were the other churches round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Methodist church and the Baptist church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was it all the same kind of people who went to them or did a different type of person go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, but just all the same. Neighbours, some'd go to one church and some to another. See it was just what had attracted them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It wasn't anything to do with how much money they had or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 The people who owned }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 crofts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 , did they have an easier life than the cotters or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I don't know, I think everybody was working pretty hard and - of course the crofts were only rented, they didn't own them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But they did have the choice of the milk and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, they did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did that make things easier for them or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well they had a lot of hard work and they had to keep working but then they did sometimes have a little extra that the cotter didn't have. But - the cotters - sometimes - well I know we did sometimes, somebody would say, here's a small 
plot, you can plant potatoes here and they - they didn't take anything for a - person like that for it. You maybe get - help them with something but - but they didn't take money for it. They would just give you and say, here's a small patch, you can you c
an plant potatoes in this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they do this to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That must have helped a bit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there any difference between craftsmen and labourers round that part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. They were generally the crofters - most of them could do some different kind of work besides just the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 crafting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
, of course it was - crofting and fishing went hand in hand but you would very often get a crofter who was a fisherman and at the same time he could build a house. Or maybe another one could build a boat. You see, they were - they were versatile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And there were a lot of skilled men around too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 There were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Who'd served their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you ever remember anybody being described as a real lady or a real gentleman, was that term used round where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You mean - a - a lady or a gentleman because they were a nice person? Or - or their rank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I meant did people use that term, if you heard somebody say she's a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 If you heard somebody say that would you have thought they were talking about their manners and ways or their rank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, no, it would have been their personality. Yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was a phrase that was used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And a real gentleman the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, would have been the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It meant how they were - how they behaved, not how they were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How - yes. Oh no, no, it was how they conducted themselves and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What particular ways did people have to behave to be thought much of in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well I think that they were kind of understanding. As much that as anything else, that they were kind of an understanding person and could - well if somebody was maybe doing something wrong or that they - th
ey would slide over it and not accuse them of doing anything and - and just acting in a - in a charitable manner. Then somebody would say, well that's a lady, or, that's a gentleman. That sort of style.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever work with anybody who was like that or know anyone who was like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I couldna name }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 anybody}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  in particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But as far as class }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 consciousness}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 , a lot of people think of themselves as middle class or working class, that didn't apply?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, not here. Not, no. People were all working people here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And they thought of themselves like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Just as ordinary working people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And then the only people who were different were the minister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And maybe the doctor and the schoolteacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But the merchants not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
No, no, the merchants - I don't think the merchants ever thought of themselves as being - upper class. No, no, they didna - the didna cut themselves off from the community. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But the doctor did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, but it was just that he was - one docto
r in a big district and I think - well - folk will take advantage of the man to - wanted to have more contact with him then other people you see. It was just - he was the doctor - and the minister was the minister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And they had another life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They were - they had to be respected. And to be looked up to in a way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there a policeman around?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 nearer than}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6754298\charrsid9600179 Sandwick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So did you ever see a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes - very occasionally. I was never frightened for a policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother ever say she'd call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She didn't do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, sometimes. Some people did but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember at that time how he treated people round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well we hardly ever saw him so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 He wasn't a feature of life really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 He wasn't much needed somehow or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 There weren't young gangs of boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Not so much now. They didn't have money then. That's money that makes the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Makes them discontented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes, and - well, if they have money they can buy drink and - then get out of hand but when they - of course I don't say that they didn't have because they could get a bottle of whisky for half a crown then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there any drunkeness around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well - it was - not very much. Maybe a - Christmas or a wedding or anything they might get something a little extra but - not gen - not terribly bad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember any family that was very poor because a lot of money was spent on drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you think your parents had a struggle to make ends meet, to manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well that I think was ever present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 In your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 We - we just knew that the - everything had to be done carefully.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother ever get any help from anything outside, like church or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Could she have done do you think if she'd wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I don't think there was anything - any provision for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was there any poor relief?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
There was - there was some kind of a - a poor relief and I think she did get for a time maybe half a crown a month or something. It was very very little, but I think she did get a little when we were very young, not long after my father died, but I c
ouldn't tell you how long that continued.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you know anything else about it, how she got it or how the people treated her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well it was something that was - really for needful people you know. But I don't know who - I don't know how it was administered. No.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Do you remember if there was somebody in the district whom people disapproved of was there any special way they showed it, do you ever remember that happening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Does the term rough music mean anything to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That was a term when people made a big noise with clattering tins driving somebody out of the community, they didn't do that here?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You were six years old when you first went to school, what time did you start school then, about nine o'clock was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. School I think started at nine well we had to leave not much after eight to - to get - to walk there for nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You stayed over for your lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And then you came back about what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 About five o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You left at five or you got home at five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
I - I think we left at five. A long day, yes. Because we had a - a break at eleven o'clock, five minutes and we had about an hour - half past twelve was it - no - it was after ten, somethi
ng after ten o'clock we had a five minute break and then it was twelve to one I think it was the dinner hour. And then we had a b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
eak again after two o'clock, five minute break. And then I think we got out at five o'clock, so it was quite a long day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What was the name of the school, did it have a name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was Boddom school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was it a church school or a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, a board school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you first went to school did you go on your own or with your chum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh with my chums.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I - I liked going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Tell me some more about it, why you liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I just liked - I seemed to like the learning. I was very fond of arithmetic. I can remember after I was finished school 
I used to take my arithmetic book and work out. Yes. And I loved the problems you know, one pipe can fill a tank in so many hours and another empty it in so many hours where there's two or three, how long does it take to empty it. I liked that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What did you think about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I was always on good terms with the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How many were there at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 We'd just two teachers. Two teacher school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember what the teachers stressed as important in general conduct and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I couldna say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they make anything of tidiness and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, well we were - we were always - at - march into the school - form up outside and - and march in and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And did you have to be tidy or didn't they care much about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, oh yes, yes, they - they wanted you to be tidy and clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they expect you to stand up when they came in a room and that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. We did, and when the inspector came. Inspector used to come -
 for the - that was a big event, yes. And if the minister come in. He used to come and visit the school. And then the - the - school officers came once a month or something to check the attendants to see if there were any delinquents. We had to stand up w
hen he came in. Anybody who wasn't attending you see then he had to go to see why they weren't attending. Of course if you were ill you had to stay home, you couldna help it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you tell me anything about the Shetland dialect, did you speak a different kind of language at all then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well a different dialect home but we spoke the kings English at the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they want you to do that at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, we were just drilled like that. Oh yes. Educated with a - a - English. But then whe
n we were outside the school we were just speaking ordinary. Dialect. That's lost a lot of it's dialect by this time. More education and more - mixing with different places and - lost a lot, yes. Shetlanders I think could always make themselves understood
 you see when they went away, if they were going away. Then you get some from the North of Scotland from the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 Moray firth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 and all like that, they never tried to alter. They just speak their own way of speaking and they never try, but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Before children went to school did they already speak some of the ordinary English?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well the most of them were beginning to read before they went to school. I could read quite a lot when I - before I went to school, I was so keen to learn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And your mother taught you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 If you did something the teachers disapproved of, what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well if you were very bad you might get the strap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What's very bad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well they didna - they didna like you maybe blotting your book or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That was very bad was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well it was considered bad, yes. You were supposed to be - keep your book tidy and clean and - you might get a - a strap for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was that what they called a tawse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. That was the tawse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they punish the girls that way too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Any other punishments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Standing in a corner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I never saw that done. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 
Of course it wasna - they weren't given tawse every day. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was just if somebody was really disobedient.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Would you say that when children got it they deserved it or was it given rather unnecessarily do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - it varied a lot by the teachers. Some of them like to throw their weight about and - and some you never saw the tawse with them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes, she was always interested in my schoolwork. Helped with my lessons at night. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't think that parents were in the habit of visiting the
 school unless they had something, maybe to - for - somebody was ill or something but - it wasna common for the parents to come to school. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do they do it more now in Shetland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I don't know, I don't - I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you know if she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  met your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Oh yes, she knew the teachers, she always knew them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They lived locally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Some of them, yes. Some of them were local.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did the other children come from similar kinds of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, all the same sort of people, yes.;;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did the teachers have any children that they treated }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 differently}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well some of them did maybe have favourites. But - some of them had no favourites at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did some of them have children they were particularly down on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well some of them might but - I just - wouldn't say anything outstanding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It's not something that sticks in your memory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Victimisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You don't remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about cliques or gangs, did they have anything like that here in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. It wasna - there was certainly maybe a few that would be friendly or - that, but they wouldna - there were no riches I mean, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were there fights in the playground?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh just like any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 other place}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  I would imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
In some schools there seem to have been groups of children from different parts of a village or a community would form a team and then fight the other, it wasn't like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't think they were very bad like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That was just the one school you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Just the one school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And you left at what age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 At - fourteen. Fourteen yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 If you could have stayed longer would you have done or were you very keen to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well - I don't think I had any inclination to go up further to school. I had no desire to be a schoolteacher. No, no. If I'd been anything, if I'd had the chance then that they have now I think I'd have gone in for nursing. Yes. In for nursing
. Or - or else dressmaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was it ever suggested to you that you could be a teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 Just - it was only a very, very few who could educate their bairns
\rquote  at that time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Now everybody is educated. So - it was only one or two who could be educated at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Because it depended upon sufficient money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever have any part time schooling afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Well - oh yes, I - I went to - to the night classes. One - one thing after I left school. Well - we d
id sewing. And - we just kind of generally - general classes but the sewing was the thing that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Attracted you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You did arithmetic there and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't - don't think so. I got what education is - carried me along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And you've educated yourself with reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You do, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you think that school was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 benefit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh it was, it certainly was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 While you were at school the first money you earned was for the two baby spencers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you earn any other money before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well just knitting. I used to knit after - when I came home from school and did my lessons, then I was knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 This was shawls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Shawls, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Anything else?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Mainly shawls but - before I was finished school they'd started knitting cardigans and - mother was very good at knitting and - several would ask her to knit them a cardigan and v
ery often she did the bodies and I did the sleeves and - I was helping along with that. And stockings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Long ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 Well, boys' stockings. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
I remember doing a pair for my brother wi'fancy turn-over tops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you sell anything in Lerwick that you knitted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes. It was only - well, no, you could see hosiery down there at Spiggie, where Spiggie hotel is now. They used to have a - a shop - there used to be a shop there, independent of the hotel, and they bought your - your shawls and things an
d then you bought your goods from them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you sold things what did you do with the money before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well you never had any money. You didn't get money for your -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You just bought things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, you didna get money, they didna give you money for your -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was exchange?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was yes, it was barter. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You never got any money for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Only the spencers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You - you - well I didna get the money for them you see, I got the - I go the wallpaper for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was like an exchange?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Yes. And if you sold - if you sold shawls in a shop and - asked for the money they'd get threepence out of every shilling. If you got the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So there was no point really?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So you only got ninepence instead of the shilling, there wasna much point in asking for the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did anybody sell things privately to well off people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well not very much at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was all done through the shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 All done through the shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did-you have any paid job before you left school, part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Your first job was working down at Sumburgh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 At }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 Sumburgh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you tell me something about the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well it was a just a kind of a kitchen maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Doing what sort of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well there were - anything - they was - there were two maids there, there was a housekeeper and a cook. So I had to help either of them and serve the meals at the - the table for the old lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How many people were living in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well they were just - they didn't live there all the time, she had a house in Edinburgh and she would - there were only just herself but she would have friends staying with her. Friends from the South stayed with her. Sometimes 
she had maybe half a dozen in the house. And she was a - one of the old type you know. Fussy to a degree.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What sort of things were they fussy about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well she was very fussy - the - maids in the kitchen didn't have to have a three course dinner, 
they'd a - they had a middle of the day dinner, they didn't have late dinner. We didn't have to have three courses, if we had soup we didn't have to have any pudding. We were always allowed the meat course but either soup or pudding but not both. And when
 she was given - she went into the storeroom every morning and gave out the stuff that had to be cooked and she would count the prunes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I felt that that was the kind of a mistress that would make dishonest maids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Because she had no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 trust}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
No. Of course I wasna experienced but the other maids that she had, they were sisters and they belonged to Edinburgh and they'd had experience. And they just did things that their own way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And she didn't know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She didn't know. But we always had three course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But it served her right really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It served her right, certainly. Certainly. But - I - I don't think she was doing any good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she an unfriendly person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She didn't talk to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not much, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you feel that she took any interest in you as a young girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You were just somebody working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. She would - come sniffing round the kitchen at night to see what 
the - after the maids had gone to bed she would be - if you wanted - if you needed tea you would put your tea caddy on the dresser. If you - your soap was getting thin you would put the bit on the dresser then she would see that she would have to give you
 out soap. If your shoe polish, you leave the empty tin. That sort of thing. And she came every night after you went to bed and put the replacements there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 That's terrible really isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Had you ever met anybody like that before you took that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No. Never - and never after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she an Edinburgh woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she mix with the local people at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well not with very many of them. She was one of the kind that felt herself above every
 body. Of course, she was married to one of the Brewsters and the Brewsters were the - the lairds. But they had - they had the big house there, at Sumburgh, but they lived in Edinburgh most of the time, just come home for - of course here husband was dead
 by that time, but they just come home for a month or two in the summertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Do you remember while you were there how much time }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 off you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  were allowed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 We didna get any time off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 None?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. We had - we had to go to church on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She forced you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, for appearance. We had prayers every morning and we had to be at prayers every morning in the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Who said the prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh she did. Oh she was - she was having maybe a - a missionary, a lay missionary stayi
ng with her or a minister or something then they took the prayers. But if she was alone she took the prayers herself. And we had to be there for prayers. And we had to go to church on Sunday. Show an appearance but - outside of that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 hypercritical}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you went to church on Sundays was that the church at Sumburgh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
It was the church here, the same church - the church here, we had to come up but she had a - a cab that she drove in and the servants in a gig.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And the servants went in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 In the gig, the open gig. She was in the cab you see. And we were in the open gig and we had to follow behind the cab.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 In the church did the rich people sit in a different part of the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well, the - the laird had a pew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 So she was in the pew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She was in that pew, yes. And then we could sit anywhere we liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she particular about what you wore to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. She didna say anything about what we had to wear but of course we were - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 d
ecently}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  dressed for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She didn't make you wear a special kind of cap or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about in the house, did you have a uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Black dress, white apron and white rubber collar and white rubber cuffs. And a white belt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you feel rebellious about it at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. We didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But her character, it's not just looking aback that it strikes you like that, at the time you thought she was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes, I knew that she was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not kindly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, she was - she was a fussy person like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were at that house where could you have to sit with the other servants and talk, did you have a room of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 We were just in the kitchen. In the kitchen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And she could come in at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh she could come in any time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have a bedroom of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did the housekeeper tell you what to do or did she come and give you your orders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I just worked with the other two you see and did what they wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You were sort of under them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 More than under her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How did you get on with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They were nice were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Very nice, they were both widows. Both widows, yes, yes. Sisters they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She had prayers and she made you go to church, did she sort of preach to you about how you were to behave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no, she didna - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You say you were allowed no free time, you mean you never had a day off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not even a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 All the time you were supposed to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 We were working all the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 For how many months was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I think it was maybe about three months or something. But I do remember her going into Lerwick, you know - tha
t was by car and - of course I'd never have had the never then to have done it on my own but the other two servants said, come on, we'-l get the work finished and - do all the work and - and we could see her when she come over the top you see, she could -
 there were only one road she could come and we could see her coming. We went - we went upstairs and sat in the drawing room 'til we saw her coming. Well it was the only way to - to get above it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You had to make a joke of it really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, yes. We 
had tea in the drawing room, sat up in the drawing room and had tea there. Then we saw the car coming and - left no dirty marks behind us so she never knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Otherwise I suppose she'd have felt it had been contaminated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did the other maids, did they ever sort of help themselves to the food, to take home or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well you see they - no, they couldn't go home, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did your mother come and visit you at the house there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well you see at that time my mother was a good bit away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Wasn't that the time when you were with your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 After we - after my grandmother had died. And my mother and brother went home. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 You see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 , again and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When your grandmother was still living you went to live }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 beside}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  her didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But you-weren't working then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You took the job after her death?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you tell me then in that household did the housekeeper have to do things like making the bread and making the jam and that ki
nd of thing, do you remember about that kind of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
They didn't do very much - of that. Yes, well they did - the cook did the baking. I don't think they did any jam much while I was there, not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about the kind of meals they had, was it very different from what you'd had before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, it was just - very ordinary, she didn't live expensively.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she have a cooked breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they keep hens and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. The - the farm house was just not very far away and they got eggs from the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about their garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
They had their own vegetables, yes. And they grew their own tomatoes. That was another thing. She never thought of giving us a tomato you know. This tomatoes was taken in an
d they were kept in the - in the dining room. And - of course they picked the best of them and then - cook or the housemaid would say, oh it's going to be tomato soup tomorrow. Small tomatoes were left, they'll be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 tomato}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  soup tomorrow. Well - she knew wher
e the key was and she went into the store room, of course everything was keys, the storerooms were all keys but she knew where the key was and she would take the key and go into the storeroom and bring down a tin of tinned tomatoes, take them into the kit
chen. That was all right. The old lady got the tinned }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 tomato}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 soup, the tomato soup made from the tinned tomatoes and we had those nice little tomatoes, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you often laugh about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh we did, yes. Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What pay did you get for that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Ten shillings a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What did you think of that at the time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - I couldna very much - it wasna very much but still it was better than nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was that a kind of usual rate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I thought it was about that time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And then you got your keep as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about the washing, how was that done in that household, who did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well - the - there was a lady come in and did the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did she have her meals with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you always have to wait 'til the old lady had her food until you had yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I think we generally }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 dodged}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  about - maybe had soup while she was having soup and - hurried - hurried it over and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What time did you have to get up, was she fussy about the time you rose in the morning
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I think maybe about seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And you got to bed about what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh maybe ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you remember anything in the house there that you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 benefited}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  from in any way, for example, were there any interesting books to read that you read there or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, she had a library and you could always get books from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She didn't mind that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you read then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I did. The one book that - I read and I never forgot again was the Hound of the Baskervilles. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about newspapers and magazines, did she have that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she a reader herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I think she was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was she an educated woman or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I imagine she would have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 But not very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about music, did she play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I never heard her play, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How long did you stay in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Just the one summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Only one summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, just the one summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Can you tell me how you actually found that job, how did you get hold of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well she wrote from Edinburgh asking me if I would take the job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How did she know about you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I don't know. Somebody must have -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 A recommendation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Must have done. Yes. Because I had a letter from her from Edinburgh asking me if I would come there when she come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Could you have done another job or was that all that was open to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well it was all that was really locally.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you consider going away from home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. Not at the time, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you left that one, was it then that you went to Spiggie Hotel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. The following summer. I was home all winter, you see, and then they asked me to come there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 While you were there in the winter did you get any money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 There was nothing to do I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And then I think you said eighteen summers you were at the Spiggie hotel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What was the pay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well the pay was ten shillings a week and the last two summers, the last two summers I got twelve and six. But then you got tips - at the hotel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did that make quite a different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It did make a difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What was the employer there, a man or woman over you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 It was - a married couple. A married couple, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 How were they - were they very nice people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh - oh yes, oh yes, they were nice, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not like she was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no, no. Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they tell you what to do, the work and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well the - the lady did most of the cooking and then the, they had a daughter, and she did some of the cooking, but we just worked together, about the house, we - we just did the work together. Making the beds, yes, making the beds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were there any other maids working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
There was one - they had cows and there was another one who - Mary looked after the cows and helped with the washing up and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 The woman who lived there, did she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 call}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  you by your first name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And what did you call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh she was Mrs. Mrs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What about the old lady at the other place, what did you call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 At the - Sumburgh - oh she was Mr Brewster. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 She didn't expect to be called madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I don't think so. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And she called you by your first name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was the housekeeper also called by her Christian name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I'm not sure, I think - I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were at Spiggie hotel did you go home at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. I slept there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you have your own room there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Well sometimes. Sometimes I slept along with the daughter when we were crowded out and at one time we slept out in a tent for a while.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Were you treated as an equal there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes, just like one of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Not like the old lady had done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you quite like working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Very - very fine to be working, you met such an awful lot of folk you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And they talked to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. But I never - spike to anybody when I was serving unless they spoke to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Was that a rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well it was - how - it was done at Sumburgh, I think that I got th
at but - at - it was only when you were spoken to you spoke when you were spoken to, and I always carried that out at Spiggie. Of course there were people there who were chatting all the time you see and you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You couldn't have got on with your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 
You - you - no, and you - but when people were speaking to you, you had to answer them back again but you didn't make conversation at the table, when you were serving the table you didn't make conversation with anybody. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You ask them maybe if they were wanting this and that but you didn't enter into a conversation with them. But then we had lots of fun you know. Oh ye did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well we would just caper around and - maybe with some of the younger visitors, they were - wel
l then there was the young ones, the little ones. They generally all came running to me to help them if they were in difficulty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 You liked playing with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. Yes. Maybe someone would fall and I - I - and tire or something and it 
was me they ran to get them cleaned again. I was great friends with all of the young people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did they have quite a wide variety of ages and all different types?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes. There'd be families coming sometimes you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 In that work did you ever have a half day or a day off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 The same there, you worked every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Every day. Not even Sunday, you did - they didn't even force me to go to the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you give up going to the church or did you still go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I 
had - I couldn't get there in the summer time when I was there but then as soon as I was home again I was back to the kirk again. Because people understood that when you were - working you couldn't be - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When did you stop going to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
I think I stopped going to Sunday school about the time that - we went to my grandmother's. I was finished with - been finished with school for a year then. And shuffling from the one place to the other but then I've done quite a lot of work with the S
unday school here. Teaching. But I've stopped that now and handed over to two younger ones who - carry it on. It's done in more modern ways now than it used to be. You know, they paint text cards and different things like that kind, it's more interesting 
for the little ones and I think it's better for the younger ones to - to take over. I certainly helped to keep the door open, when there was a kind of a - lot, there were nobody - nobody -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Nobody going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 weren't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 - the minister had gone away and - and - I thought it was too bad that - if it was going to be - if you close a door it's not so easy opened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 People go elsewhere if they want it don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 After you'd done your eighteen years there, was that when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever go back to a paid job after marriage?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No. Just always been here sort of thing. Plenty to do. Plenty to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever wish that you could do another job, I know you said you might have done nursing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Yes. But I never - yearned for it you know. No. I've never regretted that I didn't - I had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 plenty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 of it to do here. Four old folk to look after. And I thought sometimes that it was fortunate that I had an inclination like that, because it helped me over some difficult periods.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were working did you ever belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you ever have a winter job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Could you have got one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I never tried for anything you see because there was always the knitting. And - plenty -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Did you get quite a lot for that in exchange?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
Well you see in later years it got to be that you - you weren't so dependant on the shops for buying your knitting. You got - well when I was working at the hotel I got lots o
f private orders for visitors. And then you were sending it away to them and you were getting the money for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I suppose you couldn't say how much you got, was it enough to make quite a contribution?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I - oh yes, it was. And - sending it direc
t to the wearer we could get a little more for it than we would get selling it to the shop you see because you were cutting out the middle man. Now we weren't charging what they would be charging but still it was better for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 When you were working d
id you think about employers and the people they were employing as two different groups or didn't you think in that kind of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I just - I'll tell you how I looked at it when I was working that - I felt that anybody who was working at a job, the
y had to take an interest in it as if it was their own. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 You had the work - the stuff belonging to your employer as if it was your own. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 I always felt like that and - at the end of every summer I would take a day or two before I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 
 there and went a home, I would take a day or two mending all the linen, the bed linen and things like that. I put everything in repair before I went home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 They must have been grateful for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Well I've been told it wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73424\charrsid9600179 everybody}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179  that did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Would you say that working changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 No, I don't think - I just kind of carried on - which is me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13267250 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 And the sort of people you knew and your friends, were they the same over the years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850780 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2909418\charrsid9600179 Oh yes.
